# Proposition 3.3
.0. Syl_31(G) is self-centralizing and of index 6.
.1. Syl_37(G) is self-centralizing and of index 18.
.2. Syl_67(G) is self-centralizing and of index 22.

# Proof of Proposition 3.3.0
Let P ∈ Syl_31(G)
Let N := N_G(P)
Let F := |N:P|
Assert |G:P| ≡₃₁ F
Assert |C_G(P)| divides g_pi'
Assert F ≡₃₁ 6
Assert F divides 30*37*67
Then F ∈ {6, 37}
Assert F ≠ 37
Then F = 6

# Proposition 3.2
|G| = 2^8 . 3^7 . 5^6 . 7 . 11 . 31 . 37 . 67